<HEADLINE>
<P>
FLAMES DESTROY L.A.'S HISTORIC PAN PACIFIC AUDITORIUM 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
I was both saddened and appalled as I heard the fire trucks and helicopters 
trying to save the burning Pan Pacific building. This beautiful Art Deco 
building has remained empty and in disrepair for a number of years. If this 
disregard for buildings is how the people of Los Angeles treat their historic 
landmarks, then maybe the people of Los Angeles do not deserve them. 
</P>
<P>
SUSAN SCHWARTZ 
</P>
<P>
Los Angeles 
</P>
</TEXT>
