<HEADLINE>
<P>
WHAT WENT AROUND FINALLY CAME AROUND FOR RACING'S UNSERS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
I respectfully suggest that Jim Murray might be better off reviewing old 
Hollywood racing movies than irresponsibly sensationalizing the Emerson 
Fittipaldi-Al Unser Jr. incident by suggesting that it was anything but an 
accident. 
</P>
<P>
Fittipaldi did not intentionally eliminate Unser Jr. for two reasons: (1) To do 
so would have been equally dangerous to both; and (2) Fittipaldi is a 
gentleman. 
</P>
<P>
More important, neither Unser Jr. nor any of his protective relatives or team 
members has blamed the accident on anything but racing. 
</P>
<P>
TEX GUTHRIE 
</P>
<P>
Paradise Valley, Ariz. 
