<HEADLINE>
<P>
KCET TO AIR JAPAN NEWSCAST IN ENGLISH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
As part of its growing interest in Pacific Rim programming, KCET Channel 28 on 
Monday will begin airing a 30-minute Japanese newscast in English. "Today's 
Japan" will air Monday through Thursday nights at 12:05 a.m. throughout the 
summer. 
</P>
<P>
The program is produced by the Japanese network NHK for broadcast in that 
country. Norio Shimamura, general manager of NHK America, said that the 
newscast was conceived for English-speaking foreigners in Japan and for 
Japanese who are learning English, but the network found that "the quickly 
changing situation in today's Far East" had created other markets for it. 
</P>
<P>
"Today's Japan" also is carried on PBS stations in San Francisco, New York, 
Boston, Pittsburgh, Miami, Dallas, Washington and Seattle. 
</P>
</TEXT>
