<HEADLINE>
<P>
WEEKEND CHECKLIST FOR DEDICATED DIGGERS AND PLANTERS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
For dedicated gardeners, here are suggestions from the California Assn. of 
Nurserymen: 
</P>
<P>
Use stakes to support the stalks of taller gladiolus or delphiniums. 
</P>
<P>
Decorating the vegetable garden with marigold plantings seems to help keep 
snails away because of the musky smell of the foliage. 
</P>
<P>
If you're partial to Mexican food, plant some tomatillos in your garden this 
year. They're a basic ingredient in salsa verde. 
</P>
<P>
Try gerberas for a brilliant display of daisy-like flowers in a shaded border 
as a container plant or for cut flowers. 
</P>
<P>
If planting nasturtium seeds, they need total darkness, so be sure to cover the 
seeds to a depth of one-quarter inch. 
</P>
<P>
Planters that attach to the railing of an apartment or condo balcony allow 
maximum use of limited space. 
</P>
</TEXT>
