<HEADLINE>
<P>
METRO DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: ALLEGED 'SKINHEADS' DENIED LOWER BAIL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A court commissioner Friday refused to reduce the $50,000 bail set for each of 
four reputed neo-Nazi "skinheads" charged with attacking a Middle Eastern 
couple in the mistaken belief that they were Jewish. 
</P>
<P>
Defense attorneys argued that the bail was excessive, but Pomona Municipal 
Court Commissioner Joel Hoffman disagreed. The lawyers told the judge that 
their clients had strong community ties, little or no prior criminal records 
and were not likely to flee prosecution. 
</P>
<P>
But Deputy Dist. Atty. Hyatt Seligman argued that, because the defendants 
apparently "prey on anyone different from them, they represent a grave danger 
to the community." 
</P>
<P>
The commissioner ordered Scott R. Wilson, 28, of West Covina; Timothy Robert 
Zaal, 25, of Glendora; William Killackey, 21, of Yorba Linda, and his sister, 
Amy Killackey, 19, of West Covina, to remain in custody in lieu of $50,000 bail 
each. 
</P>
<P>
The four face charges in connection with the alleged attack and beating of a 
Middle Eastern couple in a La Verne grocery store parking lot May 28. 
</P>
</TEXT>
