<P>
UGANDA HOLDING 2,800 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Reuters 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
KAMPALA, Uganda 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Ugandan army is holding more than 2,800 suspected rebel sympathizers in 
prison without charges, Defense Minister Elly Tumwine told Parliament this 
week, speaking in support of legislation to establish special courts to try 
suspected rebels. 
</P>
