<HEADLINE>
<P>
HART, CERRITOS TO PLAY FOR 4-A BASEBALL TITLE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By SAM FARMER, Times Staff Writer 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A list of the top baseball teams in the Southern Section 4-A Division is taped 
to a wall in the Cerritos High dugout. As the playoffs progressed, teams that 
were eliminated were crossed off. 
</P>
<P>
Now only two -- Cerritos and Hart -- remain. 
</P>
<P>
Richard Emard, the second-year coach at Cerritos who posted the list, would 
like to cross off Hart (23-6) after the 4-A title game at 4:30 p.m. today at 
Dodger Stadium. 
</P>
<P>
To do so, Cerritos (26-6) will have to shut down a high-powered offense that 
boasts seven starters batting better than .300 and has produced 57 hits and 57 
runs in four playoff games. Mark Mattingly (10-2), a senior right-hander, will 
start for the Cerritos. Mattingly, who has three wins and a save in four 
playoff games, has lost only to Westminster, a 7-4 winner over Hart in March, 
and Lakewood, ranked 13th in the nation by USA Today. 
</P>
<P>
Center fielder Cobi Cradle, a three-year All-San Gabriel Valley League 
selection, is batting .470 and has 23 steals. Cradle, who has signed with Long 
Beach State, is one of seven starting seniors. 
</P>
<P>
Cradle is joined by Robert Hinds, a UCLA-bound shortstop who is batting .390 
and has 29 steals. Second baseman Curt Knabe is batting .410. 
</P>
</TEXT>
